""" 4.    kmeans.   (  )  .
"""
inertia = []
for i in range(1, data_normalized.shape[0]+1):
    clusters_kmeans = KMeans(n_clusters=i, 
               init = 'random',
               n_init = 100,
               max_iter = 1000).fit(data_normalized)
    inertia.append(clusters_kmeans.inertia_)

plt.plot(range(1, data_normalized.shape[0] - 310), inertia[:data_normalized.shape[0] - 311], 'bo-', marker='s')
plt.xlabel('$k$')
plt.ylabel('Objective function value')
plt.axvline(x=5, c='r')
plt.show()

"""
6.         4     (    ).    ,      .
   ,  ,    (Silhouette  ).
"""
from sklearn.metrics import silhouette_score
from scipy.spatial.distance import squareform

PDIST = pdist(data_normalized, "cityblock")

clusters_dbscan = clusters_dbscan.fit_predict (data_normalized)
clusters_kmeans = clusters_kmeans.fit_predict (data_normalized)
clusters_HDBSCAN = data_hdbscan['cluster']


print("DBSCAN:", silhouette_score(squareform(PDIST), clusters_dbscan))
print("k_means:", silhouette_score(squareform(PDIST), clusters_kmeans))
print("HDBSCAN:", silhouette_score(squareform(PDIST), clusters_HDBSCAN))
print("AgglomerativeClustering:", silhouette_score(squareform(PDIST), clusters_agglomerative))
